    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>It has been estimated that individuals with COVID-19 can shed replication-competent virus up to a maximum of twenty days after initiation of symptoms. This report describes two patients with mild forms of the disease who shed replication-competent virus for 24 and 37 days, respectively, after symptom onset.</jats:p>",
